verbose_text: To elucidate the potential mechanism by which arnebin-1 attenuated lipid accumulation and liver fibrosis during NAFLD, the levels of PPARgamma, MMP-9 and TIMP-1 proteins were examined using Western blot analyses, which demonstrated that the HFD insult significantly decreased the protein levels of PPARgamma and pro-MMP-9 compared with the control group (P < 0.05 for all comparisons), while it significantly increased the levels of TIMP-1 compared with the control group (P < 0.05).
